# ── Build output ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The multi-stage Dockerfile builds the JAR inside the container.
# We never want the local target/ dir copied into the build context — it would
# bloat the context, slow transfers, and risk shipping stale artifacts.
target/

# ── Git metadata ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.git/
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# ── GitHub Actions ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.github/

# ── IDE and OS files ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.idea/
*.iml
.vscode/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# ── Local Maven cache ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The Dockerfile uses --mount=type=cache for .m2 — the local cache is never needed.
.m2/

# ── Docker Compose (not needed inside the image) ──────────────────────────────
docker-compose*.yml

# ── Docs and test reports ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.md
docs/